Here, we see the names of different views, and we also have code snippets as

47
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:49,470
well as a preview of what they would look like on the device.

48
00:02:49,470 --> 00:02:53,120
You can always compare your code to what we have here and

49
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:55,170
see if there's any differences.

50
00:02:55,170 --> 00:02:56,800
The third technique is to use undo.

51
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,240
If you're paying attention when you type,

52
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:03,430
you should be able to see pretty quickly when you type something wrong.

53
00:03:03,430 --> 00:03:08,400
Try undoing the last few keystrokes to see if any of those fixed the error.

54
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:12,385
As we showed you before, you can hit Cmd+Z to undo a change or

55
00:03:12,385 --> 00:03:15,470
Cmd+Shift+Z to redo a change.

56
00:03:15,470 --> 00:03:20,965
On Windows, it's Ctrl+Z to undo and Ctrl+Shift+Z to redo.

57
00:03:20,965 --> 00:03:25,725
Or in the XML visualizer, we have these nice handy buttons for undo and redo.

58
00:03:25,725 --> 00:03:29,477
If you really don't know what to do, you can always hit this Reset Code button,

59
00:03:29,477 --> 00:03:32,127
which brings you back to the original code that we gave you,

60
00:03:32,127 --> 00:03:33,867
which should work.

61
00:03:33,867 --> 00:03:37,167
The fourth technique is to just ask for help.

62
